			<h2>Why we started ComplimentKarma?</h2>
			<div style="font-size:15px;">
				While working in different companies, we noticed that on day to day basis whenever employees help each other with a problem or task, they usually send an email, IM or just swing by each otherís desk to thank them, for the help they provided. Although this nice gesture of complimenting each other really make us feel good that coworkers appreciate our work, and provides a confirmation that we do add some value which helps others, but other than conveying this good feeling for a few moments these compliments donít really do much after that. These remain locked in the email or messenger waiting to be archived and never reach their full potential. Now think about the thousands of compliments earned by a professional like you, over the course of professional career.
				<br/><br/>
				More we discussed about this problem, more potential benefits we found waiting to be unlocked, by solving it. That is when we came up with the idea of ComplimentKarma.com. We thought what if we give all professionals a way to compliment each other. Not just a compliment but a quantifiable social compliment which stays with them forever, irrespective of the place they work at, and starts helping them immediately by letting them Earn Reputation, Cash Rewards and build long term Proof of Experience.
			</div>
